        jTextArea1.setText("Chalky soils are often shallow, stony and \nfree-draining, and added organic matter can \ndecompose rapidly, making them difficult to \nkeep fertile. Poor growth and yellowing leaves\n(chlorosis) are a result of the plants not being \nable to absorb iron and manganese by their \nroots.\nChalky soils can be very variable – from solid,\npure chalk or limestone, to gravelly to good, \ndeep, alkaline clay soils. They may contain \nlarge numbers of flints and large stones and \neven good chalky soils can contain lumps of \nchalk or limestone of varying sizes.");
